               <msContents>

                  <summary>Excerpts on North Africa, Syria, Egypt, Spain, and France from the
                     Turkish version of <persName key="person_21607038"><persName xml:lang="ota"
                           type="variant">سپاهی‌زاده محمد بن علی</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc" type="variant">Sipāhīzāde Mollā Meḥmed
                           bin ‘Alī</persName></persName>'s geographical work titled <title
                        xml:lang="ota" key="work_810">اوضح المسالك الی معرفة البلدان
                        والممالك</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc" key="work_810">Evżaḥu l-mesālik ilā ma‘rifeti
                        l-büldān ve-l-memālik</title>. The translation is dedicated to <persName
                        key="person_266879898"><persName xml:lang="ota" type="variant">سلطان مراد
                           الثانی</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc" type="variant" role="dte">Sulṭān Murād
                           es̠-s̠ānī</persName></persName> (i.e. <persName xml:lang="eng"
                        key="person_266879898" type="standard">Murad III, Sultan of the Turks,
                        1546-1595</persName>) and Ṣadra‘ẓam <persName key="person_72204812"
                        type="standard" role="dte">
                        <persName xml:lang="ota">صوقوللی محمد پاشا</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="eng">Ṣoḳollu Meḥmed Paşa,
                        1505-1579</persName></persName>.</summary>

